author: @lynnejamieson2063
text:
I’m not really sure that anyone should be stating categorically if a particular era was easier or more difficult unless they were being directly affected in both eras. I doubt very much that George Clooney was personally affected by McCarthyism, seeing as how he wasn’t born during the peak McCarthy era and I doubt that he will feel a great deal of personal impact now. I don’t doubt that he will be involved in humanitarian work currently and have every faith that his wife his working had but at the end of the day they can close the door to their home and feel pretty safe. 

Today’s issues to him just seem more pervasive because McCarthyism issues have always just been stories from the past, even if they were from and of people that he knew but of course today’s issues are more pervasive because they’re current and uncertain. No-one knows if this is the full extent or if things will only become worse. 

But as someone who does not live in the US and hasn’t any relatives there, the current issues and McCarthyism don’t feel too dissimilar. They both feel like a weird kind of tunnel vision, knee jerk reaction, I don’t know what I’m doing so I’m going to make the population scared of everything and become even more insular sort of thing, that is almost synonymous with the US. 

The only difference is, that we don’t know just how far Trump is going to go yet. Will the Dems be able to regain some much needed control at the midterms then start seeking impeachments for both the president and the vp with the hopes of putting a Democratic Speaker of the House in the White House? Who knows, but let’s face it, there’s never been a successful impeachment but then they also say third time lucky. Regardless of any of that daydreaming though, there is still a year and a half to go before the midterms and the Democrats need to find some decent candidates that are looking to shake things up and are actually looking to fight for the rights of the working people of the US, they need more like AOC, Bernie, Mayor Pete etc (but especially Bernie, many of us in the UK have a big soft spot for Bernie), who genuinely just want to make life a little easier for the average person instead of the wealthy…then maybe there could be an overhaul in how long campaigns are allowed to run for, how much money can be spent on them, time limits and equality in publicity, money and gifts connected with lobbying etc etc
